main event: An unidentified object resembling a bright star was observed moving in a northeast direction in Birdsboro, Pennsylvania on 29 June 1965.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 12 minutes,The object appeared to move right and left but was not identified as Echo I or Pegasus I or II,The object was observed below the Big Dipper and is considered to be possibly a satellite such as Centaur 2, Saturn 5 or Tyros 9, The object varied in speed during the observation, and the witness reported the object was still visible at 2252 local time.
witness description: The witness is from Birdsboro, Pennsylvania but other personal details are redacted.
